Product name: Antique Apothecary Bottle, Vintage Pharmacy Jar, Antique Medicine Bottle, Whitall Tatum & Company Bottle, Antique Glass Bottle
Description:
This listing is for an antique, clear glass, apothecary bottle labelled "Liq. Ferr. Perchl" . The bottle has a glass stopper with a flat round knob.
This vintage apothecary jar is marked “W.T. & Co. B” on the base. It was made by Whitall Tatum & Company between 1875 and 1901.
The bottle is in good condition but there are some areas of damage to note:
  -  staining around the bottle opening and stopper;
  -  a chip to the underside of the flat round opening to the bottle;
  -  there are air bubbles visible in the glass;

- What is Double Sided Print?
Double sided print is when the image is printed on both sides of the mug. A standard print is the image printed on one side of the mug. (When the mug is held in the right hand, the image faces away from you).
- What is Standard Print?
Standard print is the cheaper of the print options, with the image printed on the right side. When you hold the mug in your hand, the image will face your audience, and away from you. When held with your left, your fans will see the blank side of the mug, while you see design.

Description:
Saint Johns Wort Oil, St Johns Wort, Herbal Oil, Wild Harvested Herbs, Herbal Infusion, Organic Skin Care, Organic Oil, Healing Oil 
Saint John's Wort Oil
This plant has been used as a herbal remedy for its anti-inflammatory and healing properties since the Middle Ages. Many ancient herbalists, including Hippocrates and Pliny, recorded the medicinal properties of St. John's wort. It was noted for its wound-healing and diuretic properties as well as for the treatment of back pain. Also the plant was used as a balm for burns. The oil of the plant, also, was popular during this time. An olive oil extract of the fresh flowers that acquires a reddish color has been applied externally to relieve inflammation and promote healing. Its topical application is believed to be particularly useful in the management of hemorrhoids. In Greece the plant is known as Spathohorto which means Sword Herb. The name came from the Spartans as they used it to heal the wounds caused from swords during battles. 
Weight: 5 oz (150 ml) or 2.90 oz (85 ml)
The Saint John's Wort used is wild harvested by us and extracted in organic extra virgin olive oil (from our very own olive trees).
